cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a novel 3D face recognition algorithm using a deep convolutional neural network (DCNN) and a 3D augmentation technique. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning and fine-tuning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed 3D augmentation technique involves synthesizing different facial expressions from a single 3D face scan, which could also be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the use of large-scale labeled training data, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability of the proposed method for large databases, which could be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics).
